rally Non-Execution So We Stop Burning Heartbeats Expecting Live Trade Path Evidence\n\n**Task:** Re-check the current live PM bot behavior overnight and verify whether the repeated lack of execution evidence is a malfunction or simply the intended strategy posture.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- In the recent live PM bot window, `OUTSIDE_ACTIVE_HOURS` fired **154** times.\n- The latest repeated live blocker is explicitly:\n  - `No trade: OUTSIDE_ACTIVE_HOURS (03 UTC)`\n- Wrote structural-state artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v10m-overnight-hours-are-structurally-non-execution.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is worth pinning down because it changes how we should use overnight heartbeats. The PM bot is not broken overnight, it is intentionally in watch mode. That means expecting execution-side evidence at 03 UTC is the wrong mental model and leads to wasted debugging loops.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Treat overnight PM as **structurally non-execution**.\n- Do not use overnight heartbeats to demand live PM entry-path evidence unless active hours are changed",
